{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Automobile dealership brought action against manufacturer in state court, claiming that manufacturer had engaged in unfair or deceptive acts or practices in violation of state statutes. Following removal, manufacturer filed motion to dismiss, or, in the alternative, to compel arbitration pursuant to parties\rquote  agreements. The United States District Court for the District of Massachusetts, 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://wwwtest.int.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=h&pubNum=176284&cite=0118840301&originatingDoc=Ic8e70d6f944511d993e6d35cc61aab4a&refType=RQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.Search)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Robert B. Collings
}}}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
, United States Magistrate Judge, 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://wwwtest.int.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=1997097709&pubNum=345&originatingDoc=Ic8e70d6f944511d993e6d35cc61aab4a&refType=RP&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.Search)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
959 F.Supp. 52,
}}}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 granted motion and dismissed case. Dealership appealed. The Court of Appeals, 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://wwwtest.int.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=h&pubNum=176284&cite=0263115601&originatingDoc=Ic8e70d6f944511d993e6d35cc61aab4a&refType=RQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.Search)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Stahl
}}}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
, Circuit Judge, as a matter of apparent first impression in its circuit, held that it lacked jurisdiction over appeal.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
