{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Under general rule governing what constitutes final decision for purposes of appeal, under Federal Arbitration Act (FAA), of order favoring arbitration, order compelling arbitration is not final, and therefore not immediately reviewable, if arbitrability issue is \u8220\'3fembedded,\u8221\'3f in that issues other than propriety of arbitration are raised or relief other than determination as to arbitrability of dispute is sought. 
}
