{\*\bkmkstart co_anchor_Ia2cfce759b7f11eabea3f0dc9fb69}{\*\bkmkend co_anchor_Ia2cfce759b7f11eabea3f0dc9fb69}
\par 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Plaintiff-appellant Seacoast Motors of Salisbury, Inc. (\u8220\'3fSeacoast\u8221\'3f) appeals from a district court order dismissing its complaint and compelling arbitration.
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 We hold that we lack jurisdiction to review the propriety of the district court\rquote s non-final, \u8220\'3fembedded\u8221\'3f order compelling arbitration.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_anchor_Ia2cfce769b7f11eabea3f0dc9fb69}{\*\bkmkend co_anchor_Ia2cfce769b7f11eabea3f0dc9fb69}
\par 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_anchor_Ia2cfce769b7f11eabea3f0dc9fb69}{\*\bkmkend co_anchor_Ia2cfce769b7f11eabea3f0dc9fb69}
\par 
{\b0 \qc \cf1 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa200 \sb600 
I. FACTS AND PRIOR PROCEEDINGS
\par 
}
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
On October 21, 1991, Seacoast, an automobile dealership, and Chrysler Corporation (\u8220\'3fChrysler\u8221\'3f) entered into five agreements authorizing Seacoast to sell and service new Chrysler motor vehicles in Salisbury, Massachusetts. By the terms of the agreements, all disputes had to be submitted to arbitration.
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_B00211998104702_ID0EMLAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_B00211998104702_ID0EMLAE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_B00211998104702_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
1
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 On February 6, 1996, Chrysler notified Seacoast that it intended to establish a new Chrysler dealership in nearby Haverhill, Massachusetts. In response, on August 9, 1996, Seacoast filed a complaint in the Essex County Superior Court alleging that, by seeking to establish a dealership in Seacoast\rquote s market area, Chrysler had engaged in unfair or deceptive acts or practices in violation of Mass. Gen. Laws ch. 93B. Seacoast sought to enjoin establishment of the new franchise and to recover damages, fees, and costs.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
On August 22, 1996, Chrysler removed the case to federal court based on diversity jurisdiction. Shortly thereafter, relying on 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://wwwtest.int.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000546&cite=9USCAS3&originatingDoc=Ic8e70d6f944511d993e6d35cc61aab4a&refType=LQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.Search)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
sections 3
}}}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 and 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://wwwtest.int.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000546&cite=9USCAS4&originatingDoc=Ic8e70d6f944511d993e6d35cc61aab4a&refType=LQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.Search)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
4
}}}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 of the Federal Arbitration Act (\u8220\'3fFAA\u8221\'3f), 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://wwwtest.int.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000546&cite=9USCAS1&originatingDoc=Ic8e70d6f944511d993e6d35cc61aab4a&refType=LQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.Search)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
9 U.S.C. \u167\'3f\u167\'3f 1
}}}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u8211\'3f
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://wwwtest.int.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000546&cite=9USCAS16&originatingDoc=Ic8e70d6f944511d993e6d35cc61aab4a&refType=LQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.Search)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
16
}}}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
, Chrysler moved for \u8220\'3fan order dismissing or, alternatively, staying the action and compelling the plaintiff ... to proceed with arbitration.\u8221\'3f Seacoast opposed the motion on the ground that arbitration in this case would contravene public policy. Pursuant to an agreement between the parties, the case was transferred to a magistrate judge, who, on April 22, 1997, dismissed the case with costs and compelled arbitration. Seacoast now appeals the dismissal.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_anchor_Ia2cfce779b7f11eabea3f0dc9fb69}{\*\bkmkend co_anchor_Ia2cfce779b7f11eabea3f0dc9fb69}
\par 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_anchor_Ia2cfce779b7f11eabea3f0dc9fb69}{\*\bkmkend co_anchor_Ia2cfce779b7f11eabea3f0dc9fb69}
\par 
{\b0 \qc \cf1 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa200 \sb600 
II. DISCUSSION
\par 
}
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_anchor_F11998104702_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b1 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
[1]
}}}
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\*\bkmkstart co_anchor_B11998104702_1}{\*\bkmkend co_anchor_B11998104702_1}
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Seacoast urges us to review the propriety of the lower court\rquote s order, which both dismissed the action and compelled arbitration. The question that we must address initially is whether appellate jurisdiction attaches to the court\rquote s order compelling arbitration. We conclude that the order was interlocutory, and that we therefore lack jurisdiction to review it.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_anchor_F21998104702_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b1 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
[2]
}}}
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\*\bkmkstart co_anchor_B21998104702_1}{\*\bkmkend co_anchor_B21998104702_1}
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://wwwtest.int.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000546&cite=9USCAS3&originatingDoc=Ic8e70d6f944511d993e6d35cc61aab4a&refType=LQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.Search)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Section 3
}}}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 of the FAA provides that, when an action implicates an issue covered by an arbitration agreement between the parties, the district court, at the request of any party, \u8220\'3fshall ... stay the trial of the action until such arbitration has been had in accordance with the terms of the agreement.\u8221\'3f 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://wwwtest.int.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000546&cite=9USCAS3&originatingDoc=Ic8e70d6f944511d993e6d35cc61aab4a&refType=LQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.Search)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
9 U.S.C. \u167\'3f 3
}}}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://wwwtest.int.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000546&cite=9USCAS4&originatingDoc=Ic8e70d6f944511d993e6d35cc61aab4a&refType=LQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.Search)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Section 4
}}}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 provides that any party to an arbitration agreement may petition the district court for an order compelling arbitration, irrespective of any ongoing proceeding. 
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
See 
}
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
id.
}
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 \u167\'3f 4. Appellate review of orders that favor arbitration\u8212\'3fthat is, 
}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\*\bkmkstart co_pp_sp_506_628_1}{\*\bkmkend co_pp_sp_506_628_1}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
*628
}
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 orders that stay an action pending arbitration pursuant to 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://wwwtest.int.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000546&cite=9USCAS3&originatingDoc=Ic8e70d6f944511d993e6d35cc61aab4a&refType=LQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.Search)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
section 3
}}}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 or compel arbitration under 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://wwwtest.int.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000546&cite=9USCAS4&originatingDoc=Ic8e70d6f944511d993e6d35cc61aab4a&refType=LQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.Search)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
section 4
}}}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u8212\'3fis proscribed, if those orders are \u8220\'3finterlocutory.\u8221\'3f 
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
See 
}
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
id.
}
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 \u167\'3f 16(b)(1) & (2). Under 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://wwwtest.int.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000546&cite=9USCAS16&originatingDoc=Ic8e70d6f944511d993e6d35cc61aab4a&refType=RB&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.Search)#co_pp_28cc0000ccca6" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf25 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
section 16(a)(3)
}}}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
, however, an appellate court may review the merits of orders that favor arbitration, if those orders are \u8220\'3ffinal decision[s].\u8221\'3f 
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Id.
}
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 \u167\'3f 16(a)(3). Thus, whether a particular order favoring arbitration is appealable depends on whether it is final or interlocutory.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
